[{:db/id -1, :adr/id "adr-2605261045", :adr/title "manabi (学び) — Education Tier-B Actor R0 Scaffold", :adr/status "proposed", :adr/doc_type "adr", :adr/source-format "edn", :adr/body "\n# ADR-2605261045: manabi (学び) — Education Tier-B Actor R0 Scaffold\n\n**Date**: 2026-05-26\n**Status**: PROPOSED\n**Deciders**: Jun Kawasaki (author), Council Lv6+ (ratify), Council education advisory ≥1 lifelong-learning practitioner + ≥1 inquiry-pedagogy expert for R1+\n**ADR Hierarchy**: Parent = ADR-2605261000 (Liberation Ladder — L4 literacy/civics + L5 advanced + vocational gates). Sibling to mitate / yakushi / hagukumi / mitsuho / hikari.\n\n## Context\n\nADR-2605261000 (Liberation Ladder) gates Stage L4 (Care Tier) on manabi R2 (literacy + civics + basic-numeracy) and Stage L5 (Vocation Tier) on manabi R3 (advanced + vocational + lifelong). Without an education actor, adherents cannot acquire the skill substrate needed to (a) understand the charter they sign onto, (b) participate in 1-SBT-1-vote governance with informed consent, (c) transition out of wage-labor commute via L5 vocational substrate.\n\nExisting tooling (baien-distill, gemma-coder-distill, joucho organism agents, mitate self-care PWA) embodies pedagogy implicitly — but pedagogy as a *first-class religious-corp domain* with constitutional gates, anti-credentialism invariant, and anti-addiction UX has no actor.\n\n## Proposal\n\nLaunch **`manabi` (学び — \"learning\", continuative noun of 学ぶ \"to learn\"; multi-generational lifelong-learning echo; etymologically rooted in 真似ぶ \"to imitate/emulate\", suggesting learning-as-following-model)** as a Tier-B religious-corp actor:\n\n- **Actor DID**: `did:web:etzhayyim.com:manabi`\n- **Namespace**: `com.etzhayyim.manabi.*`\n- **R0 scope**: Open-curriculum knowledge transmission across literacy (reading + writing), numeracy (counting → calculus), civics (charter + governance + history), vocational (practical skills aligned to L5+ adherent productive contribution), lifelong inquiry (open-ended questioning + critical analysis). **Excludes**: formal accreditation, degree issuance, examination-as-gatekeeper, behavioral conditioning, for-profit textbook publishing, proprietary LMS, surveillance edtech, replacement of family/cultural transmission, advertising, political-party content.\n- **R0 robotics**: None. Education is primarily digital substrate (text + audio + open data) + (R2+) human tutors + (R3+) Yutori telepresence inheritance from hagukumi.\n- **14 gates + 10 non-goals** declared before capability lands.\n- **5 Pregel cells** (literacy, numeracy, civics+charter, vocational, lifelong inquiry) — all import-time RuntimeError in R0.\n\n## Rationale\n\n1. **Domain separation**: Pedagogy (cognitive science + curriculum design + anti-addiction UX + accessibility) is its own actor; mitate handles diagnosis, yakushi handles drugs, hagukumi handles care delivery.\n2. **L4 + L5 gate dependency**: ADR-2605261000 §6 cannot advance to L4 (literacy/civics) or L5 (vocational/advanced) without manabi R2/R3.\n3. **Anti-credentialism is constitutional**: §2(e) anti-gatekeeping forbids degree-as-employment-gate. manabi delivers *knowledge*, not credentials. State accreditation = N1 explicit non-goal.\n4. **Multi-generational invariant**: §1.3 priority + lifelong learning means manabi serves under-18 + over-65 + middle adults equally. No \"age-out\" of learning eligibility.\n5. **Anti-addiction UX is constitutional**: §2(d) Wellbecoming forbids gamification + streaks + variable rewards. manabi reference UX is calm-state-default (mirrors hagukumi G13 + mitate G11).\n\n## Design\n\n### Actor Manifest\n\n```\n20-actors/manabi/\n├── README.edn                     # Overview + R0 scope + anti-credentialism invariant\n├── CLAUDE.md                     # Actor-local instructions\n├── manifest.jsonld               # DID + cell catalog\n└── cells/                        # 5 cell scaffolds (import-time RuntimeError)\n    ├── literacy/\n    ├── numeracy/\n    ├── civics_charter/\n    ├── vocational/\n    └── lifelong_inquiry/\n```\n\n### Pregel Cells (5, all import-time RuntimeError R0)\n\n| Cell | Purpose | Murakumo node | Input | Output |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| `literacy` | Reading + writing curriculum across languages (EN + JA + adherent-native at scale) | levi (verification + curriculum integrity) | learnerDid, languageTarget, currentLevel | learningSessionAttestation (encrypted aggregate) |\n| `numeracy` | Counting → arithmetic → algebra → geometry → calculus, inquiry-based | levi | learnerDid, currentLevel | learningSessionAttestation |\n| `civics_charter` | etzhayyim Charter + governance + multi-gen ethics + comparative religion + history | levi (charter-paired) | learnerDid, charterSection | learningSessionAttestation + charterUnderstandingAttestation |\n| `vocational` | Practical-skill curriculum aligned to L5 adherent productive contribution (e.g., mitsuho farming, tatekata building, hikari maintenance, yakushi quality-control) | levi | learnerDid, skillTarget | learningSessionAttestation + skillAttestation |\n| `lifelong_inquiry` | Open-ended questioning + critical analysis + research methodology (no fixed curriculum; learner-led) | levi | learnerDid, inquiryTopic | learningSessionAttestation |\n\n### Lexicons (4, deferred to R1+)\n\n```\ncom.etzhayyim.manabi.{\n  curriculumAttestation,          # Curriculum module declaration (open-source content CID + reviewer attestations)\n  learningSessionAttestation,     # Per-session record (aggregate only for under-18; full encrypted for adult)\n  charterUnderstandingAttestation,  # Specific to civics_charter — adherent informed-consent baseline\n  silenEducationReview            # Council attestation scope (pedagogy + accessibility + anti-addiction)\n}\n```\n\n**Structural anti-surveillance enforcement**: For under-18 learners, `learningSessionAttestation` accepts only aggregate-level fields (sessionDuration, moduleId, completionFraction) — **no learner-level performance data, no error logs, no behavioral signals**. Schema rejects any per-learner detail field for minors (G6 enforcement).\n\n### Constitutional Gates (G1–G14, IMMUTABLE per R0)\n\n| Gate | Requirement | Rationale |\n|---|---|---|\n| **G1** | All curriculum content open-source (Apache 2.0 + Charter Rider) on IPFS with CID-pinned attestation | §2(e) anti-gatekeeping + ADR-2605192200 |\n| **G2** | No advertising in any learning material; no commercial-product placement; no sponsored content | §2(b) constitutional invariant |\n| **G3** | No algorithmic addiction patterns — **no streaks, no daily-login rewards, no variable-reward schedules, no FOMO triggers, no leaderboards, no badges-as-status** | §2(d) Wellbecoming + anti-attention-economy |\n| **G4** | Charter alignment — all curriculum reviewed by Council Lv6+ ≥3 for: multi-generational priority, anti-individualism, Wellbecoming alignment, non-eschatology (no millenarian content; ADR-2605192100 §1.15) | Constitutional alignment |\n| **G5** | Multilingual — minimum EN + JA at all levels; expand to adherent-native language at ≥10-adherent-per-language threshold | Adherent access equity |\n| **G6** | **Zero data collection on minors** — under-18 learner sessions emit aggregate-only attestations (see Pregel cell §design); learner identity hashed + 30-day-rotating-pseudonym (ADR-2605181200) for sessions emitted at all | Child privacy invariant |\n| **G7** | Anti-credentialism — manabi issues **no degrees, no transcripts, no GPA-equivalent**; only `skillAttestation` (subject-specific, replayable demonstration). Adherent productive contribution at L5 uses `skillAttestation`, not credentials | §2(e) constitutional invariant |\n| **G8** | No proprietary curriculum — all modules CC-BY-SA or Apache 2.0 + Rider; no exclusive vendor licenses | §2(e) + license invariant |\n| **G9** | No for-profit textbook royalties — all royalties flow to author DIDs via TitheRouter (10% to Public Fund); textbook adoption never gated by purchase | §2(e) + §2(b) |\n| **G10** | No examination-as-coercion — assessment is **self-paced demonstration**, not time-limited high-stakes testing. No proctoring. No ID-verification gating completion | §2(d) Wellbecoming + anti-test-anxiety |\n| **G11** | Lifelong — no age-out, no age-floor (except minors G6 privacy). 6-year-old and 86-year-old see same curriculum surfaces with developmentally-appropriate UX (font, pacing, scaffolding) | §1.3 multi-gen |\n| **G12** | No political indoctrination — civics_charter teaches etzhayyim charter principles + comparative political/religious systems; no advocacy for any state political party, no electoral mobilization | §1.12 routing-around-state invariant |\n| **G13** | Inquiry-based pedagogy — at least 30% of every curriculum module is open-question / learner-led (no all-direct-instruction modules) | §2(d) Wellbecoming + cognitive autonomy |\n| **G14** | Family/cultural transmission is **primary**; manabi is supplementary. No religious doctrine taught as exclusive truth; comparative-religion approach mandated for any religion module (including etzhayyim's own charter) | §1.3 multi-gen + anti-individualism cultural humility |\n\n### Non-Goals (N1–N10, EXCLUDE from R0–R3)\n\n| # | Non-Goal | Deferral |\n|---|---|---|\n| **N1** | Formal accreditation / state-recognized diplomas — state domain | Never (constitutional carve-out) |\n| **N2** | Degree issuance — anti-credentialism invariant | Never |\n| **N3** | Examination-as-gatekeeper / high-stakes proctored testing | Never |\n| **N4** | Behavioral conditioning — operant, classical, or social — applied to learners | Never |\n| **N5** | For-profit textbook publishing — §2(b) + §2(e) | Never |\n| **N6** | Proprietary LMS / closed-source learning platform | Never |\n| **N7** | Surveillance edtech — keystroke tracking, gaze tracking, learner-behavior signal mining | Never |\n| **N8** | Replacement of family / cultural / religious-of-origin transmission — manabi is supplementary | Never |\n| **N9** | Advertising / sponsored content / corporate partnerships in curriculum | Never |\n| **N10** | Political party content / electoral mobilization | Never |\n\n## Roadmap\n\n| Phase | Date | Scope | Murakumo fleet | Gate |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| **R0** | 2026-05-26 | Scaffold only. 5 cells import-time RuntimeError. | No deployment | This ADR (PROPOSED) |\n| **R1** | post-Council | Open-curriculum publishing — IPFS-pinned literacy + civics_charter modules + numeracy starter set; ≤100 adherent registered learners (advisory consumption only, no live tutoring) | levi (single node, low compute) | Future ADR + ≥1 inquiry-pedagogy practitioner on Council |\n| **R2** | post-R1 | Live human tutor sessions + vocational scaffolding aligned to mitsuho/tatekata/hikari/yakushi R2 work; ≤25,000 learner ceiling. **L4 gate eligibility.** | levi (single node) | Future ADR + 30-day public comment + ≥3 community-attested tutor cohort |\n| **R3** | post-R2 | Full vocational pipeline + lifelong inquiry mesh + Yutori telepresence (hagukumi inheritance); ≤100,000 learner ceiling. **Required for L4 → L5.** | levi + (Yutori-mediated) joseph (manipulator for vocational demonstration) | Future ADR + 60-day public review + Council multi-domain vote |\n\n## Robotics Class\n\nR0–R2: human educators only. R3: Yutori telepresence inheritance from hagukumi (no manabi-specific robotics); optional Hitogata humanoid (R3+) for vocational physical-skill demonstration. Per ADR-2605260230 hanami precedent, any new manabi-specific robot class requires separate mech-design ADR.\n\n## Murakumo Placement (R2+ design-only)\n\n- **levi**: curriculum integrity + session attestation + charter understanding verification (low compute; education is content-distribution-heavy, not compute-heavy)\n\n(Smallest fleet footprint of any Tier-B actor — manabi is fundamentally a content-distribution + human-tutor coordination actor, not a compute-intensive one.)\n\n## Consequences\n\n**Positive**:\n- L4 + L5 gates of Liberation Ladder unblock once manabi R2/R3 deploys.\n- Anti-credentialism becomes operational, not aspirational — adherent productive contribution at L5 uses skillAttestation, no degree wall.\n- Children of adherents have a multi-generational learning substrate that's structurally anti-surveillance (G6) and anti-addiction (G3).\n- Charter understanding (civics_charter cell) becomes a *real* informed-consent baseline for SBT issuance — adherents demonstrably understand what they're signing onto.\n\n**Negative / risks**:\n- G7 (no credentials) creates labor-market friction if adherents need external (non-religious-corp) employment at L4-L5 transition; mitigation: §1 ladder positions wage-labor reduction as goal, not retention; external employment compatibility is not a manabi design constraint.\n- G3 (no addictive UX) makes adherent learning engagement harder to bootstrap; mitigation: inquiry-based pedagogy + lifelong-friendly pacing optimizes for sustained autonomous motivation, slower start but durable\n- G14 (comparative-religion, no etzhayyim-as-exclusive-truth) sets a higher bar than most religious organizations; may slow doctrinal adherent depth at scale; constitutional, not adjustable\n- Curriculum content review (G4 Council Lv6+ ≥3) is a bottleneck; mitigation: parallel multi-Council-member review queue\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n1. **Extend mitate to teach symptom-screening to adherents (folded into self-care PWA)** — partially yes (mitate already does); but full literacy / numeracy / civics / vocational scope exceeds mitate; separate actor required.\n2. **Adopt Khan Academy / Wikipedia content directly without forking** — partially yes (open-license content reuse encouraged); but Charter Rider review (G4) is mandatory; manabi forks + reviews, doesn't redirect to upstream.\n3. **Provide accreditation as opt-in feature for adherents wanting state-recognized credentials** — rejected: §2(e) + N1; would re-credentialize the substrate manabi is constitutionally anti.\n4. **Adaptive AI-tutor as primary delivery (Yutori-equivalent automated)** — rejected: human-in-loop principle from hagukumi G9 extends to manabi; AI-mediated learning permitted as supplement, not primary delivery.\n\n## References\n\n- ADR-2605261000 (Liberation Ladder — L4 + L5 gates)\n- ADR-2605192100 (Mission Charter — anti-individualism + multi-gen + non-eschatology)\n- ADR-2605192200 (Charter Rider — pedagogy alignment + open-source content license)\n- ADR-2605181200 (rotating pseudonym DID — minor learner identity)\n- ADR-2605260100 (mitate — self-care PWA pedagogy precedent)\n- ADR-2605260230 (hanami robot mech-design — precedent for any future manabi robotics ADR)\n", :adr/path "90-docs/adr/2605261045-manabi-education-tier-b-actor-r0.edn", :adr/source-repo "root", :adr/topic "manabi-education", :adr/last_verified "2026-05-26", :adr/date "2026-05-26", :adr/authoritative true, :adr/related ["adr-2605261000" "adr-2605192100-etzhayyim-mission-charter" "adr-2605192200-etzhayyim-ip-free-release-charter-rider" "adr-2605260100-mitate-diagnostic-routing-charter"], :adr/authoritative_for ["manabi actor charter (R0)" "education domain constitutional gates G1..G14" "L4 + L5 education-delivery substrate"]}]
